==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nano-
<hw>nan"o-</hw> <pr>(n⟦acr⟧n"⟦osl⟧-)</pr>, <pos>pref.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A prefix meaning <sig>one-billionth</sig>; <as>as, a
<ex>nano</ex>gram is one-thousandth of a microgram</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Very small; submicroscopic; -- used to designate
sizes smaller than those that would be referred to as
<contr>micro-</contr>; <as>as, <ex>nano</ex>scale
manipulations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nanotechnology</ent>⟦br⟧
